article.headline: Tennessee Tech 110, Bluefield College 69
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Fisher scored 18 points and 13 teammates also scored in Tennessee Tech's 110-69 victory Monday night over Bluefield. Tech (1-0) led 50-32 at halftime and built the margin to 42 points with 2:40 left. Amadi McKenzie added 14 points for Tech, Belton Rivers had 13 and Rashaud Nixon 11. Bluefield (3-3) was led by James Chapman with 19 points and Robert Sharpe with 15. No other Rams' player scored in double figures. Tech shot 51.2 percent from the floor, and 54.5 percent in the second half, to 30.4 percent for the Rams. The Golden Eagles controlled the boards, 58-36.
